        <h2 style="font-size:medium;font-weight: bold;font-size: larger">How to Login in the system or application?<br></h2>
        <p style="font-weight:500;font-size: large">For Login first you have to sign up into the application in the sign up page(Which is at the left corner). For sign up you need to provide all the information correctly and also set your password correctly. After filling the form details correctly,do not forget to check the uncheck box which tells that you are agreed with all the terms and conditions for the registration. 
            Then lastly click on the Register button so that your details are registered. After registration you will receive a mail in your provided Email-Id for the final step of validation and registration. Then you can finally login into web application providing your user-id and password which you have set. <br>
        <h4 style="font-weight: bolder">NOTE:Please provide a valid Email-Id.</h4>  </p><br>
    
         <h2 style="font-size:medium;font-weight: bold;font-size: larger">Will the user or patient receive the confirmation message, after making an appointment?<br></h2>
            <p style="font-weight: 500;font-size: large">Yes, the patient will receive the confirmation about the appointment via email, specifying the details about appointment time, location,date, day and the Doctor chosen.</p><br>
         
         <h2 style="font-size:medium;font-weight: bold;font-size: larger">What happens if two user or patient choose the same appointment at the same time?<br></h2>
            <p style="font-weight: 500;font-size: large">The first patient to select the appointment will be allocated with the space. The second patient to select the appointment will be advised that the appointment is no longer available, and to choose chose another appointment time.   </p><br>
     
    
